  "text": "The function of FFLs generally depends on the type and relative activity of each regulation, and, thus is less evident than feedback loops. However, several types of FFLs have been theoretically studied [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Coherent FFLs can confer robust signal transduction, and incoherent loops also can assure transient activation of an EP against signal input.",
